The pure-strategy Nash equilibrium strategy profile is (profiles are)
\begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph*)]
     \item Both playing Reject is the only equilibrium.
	\item If $b$ is large enough, Both play Accept; otherwise both play Reject.
     \item There are two: in one, both Declare, and in the other, both Reject.
     \item There are two: in both, the countries do the opposite of each other.
    \item  There are none, only mixed strategy equilibria.
